did.unittitle: Kevin Kennedy Ephemera and Photographs Collection

physdesc.extent: in 20 record cartons, 5 legal sized manuscript boxes, 1 flat box, 1 oversized flat box, and 2 shared oversized flat boxes.

did.abstract: Kevin Kennedy (1937-2016) was a native of County Galway in Ireland and worked as a photographer in New York City, contributing to publications like The Irish Echo. Kennedy was affiliated with Irish civic organizations like the United Irish Counties Association and the New York County chapter of the Ancient Order of Hibernians. He was also devoted to fundraising on behalf of the Irish Guide Dogs for the Blind. This collection consists of photographs, photo negatives, newspapers, magazines, newspaper clippings, social event programs, religious booklets, church related materials, artifacts, correspondence, and a scrapbook.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Kevin Kennedy Ephemera and Photographs Collection is composed of materials collected by Kevin Kennedy that documents the New York Irish community, circa 1960s-early 2000s. The collection consists of photographs, photo negatives, newspapers, magazines, newspaper clippings, social event programs, religious booklets, church related materials, artifacts, prayer cards, correspondence, and a scrapbook.

Some of the materials found in this collection document important Irish civic organizations like the United Irish Counties Association, the New York County chapter of the Ancient Order of Hibernians, the Knights of Columbus, and the Friendly Sons of St. Patrick, as well as Irish charities important to Kennedy like the Irish Guide Dogs for the Blind and the Kennedy Child Study Center in New York City.
The photographs and photo negatives in this collection largely focus on events.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The materials in this collection were acquired from Kevin Kennedy's Manhattan apartment by Marion Casey in 2007.

userestrict.head: Use Restrictions
userestrict.p: Copyright (and related rights to publicity and privacy) to materials in this collection are held by Kevin Kennedy. Permission to publish or reproduce materials to which he holds copyright must be secured from the copyright holder. Please contact the Tamiment Library for assistance with contacting Kevin Kennedy.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is arranged in two series:
Series I: Kevin Kennedy Ephemera and Personal Materials
Series II: Photographs and Photo Negatives
Within each series, materials are organized in alphabetical order.

bioghist.head: Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Kevin Kennedy (1937-2016) was a native of County Galway in Ireland and worked as a photographer in New York City, contributing to publications like The Irish Echo. Kennedy was affiliated with Irish civic organizations like the United Irish Counties Association and the New York County chapter of the Ancient Order of Hibernians. He was also devoted to fundraising on behalf of the Irish Guide Dogs for the Blind.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: The Kevin Kennedy Ephemera and Photographs Collection is comprised of materials collected by Kevin Kennedy that were provided to New York University by Marion Casey in 2007. At the time of accessioning, the collection was not processed or arranged.

The collection was processed and described by an archivist in the fall of 2021. During processing, duplicate and commercially published materials were removed from the collection. Materials were placed in new acid-free folders and boxes. Original titles were retained when available. Photographs and photo negatives were kept in their original envelopes and albums and then placed into archival folders.

In November 2022, the Conservation Lab disbound and rehoused a scrapbook from the collection, which is now stored in folders in boxes 27 and 28. The order of items and pages within the scrapbook was maintained during the transfer to folders.

separatedmaterial.head: Separated Materials
separatedmaterial.p: In 2021, Irish American newspapers and periodicals were removed from the Kevin Kennedy Ephemera and Photographs collection and placed in to the Guide to the Archives of Irish America Newspapers and Periodicals Collection (AIA.004).

did.unittitle: Series I: Kevin Kennedy Ephemera and Personal Materials

physdesc.extent: in 5 legal size manuscript boxes, 1 flat box, 1 oversized box, and 2 shared oversized boxes

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains materials collected by Kevin Kennedy that focus upon the New York Irish community, circa 1960s-early 2000s. Some of the materials document important Irish organizations like the United Irish Counties Association, the New York County chapter of the Ancient Order of Hibernians, and the Friendly Sons of St. Patrick, as well as charitable organizations that were important to Kennedy like the Irish Guide Dogs for the Blind and the Kennedy Child Study Center in New York City. This series also contains some religious materials including prayer cards and programs from different churches commemorating various events, as well as newspapers and newsclippings, some of which feature Kennedy's published photographs.

Series II: Photographs and Photo Negatives

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains photographs and photo negatives covering a variety of subjects such as: St. Patrick's Day Parades, Ancient Order of the Hibernians events, United Irish Counties events, Knight of Columbus events, Ireland, Irish football clubs, weddings, and church events.
The collection also contains photographs of Mayor Ed Koch, Gerry Adams, Governor Mario Cuomo, Governor George Pataki, and President Bill Clinton.
